    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5152</citedRange></bibl>, from 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#pacho1827"/>, pl. <citedRange>66, 7</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2013"/>, pp. <citedRange>181-183</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>64.2015</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>64.2020</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>007000</citedRange></bibl>.
                Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2015b"/>, pp. <citedRange>33-34</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>65.2013</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2020"/>, p. <citedRange>245-248</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="Ἀλκάνωρ">Ἀλκάνορος</name></persName> ἁ <w lemma="ὀπά">ὀπὰ</w> <w lemma="ἴδιος">ἰδία</w>
                    <lb n="2"/>καὶ <w lemma="τάφος">τά<unclear>φ</unclear>ο<supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></w> <supplied reason="lost">καὶ</supplied> <w lemma="σορός">σορός</w>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem resp="#cdl2013">Ἀλκάνορος</lem>
                    <rdg resp="#pacho1827"><orig>ΑΜΚΑΝΟΡΟΣ</orig></rdg>
                    <rdg resp="#CIG">Ἀ<unclear>λ</unclear>κάνορος</rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="1"><lem resp="#cdl2013">ἁ ὀπὰ ἰδία</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#pacho1827"><orig>αοτιμιδια</orig></rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#CIG"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="2"><lem resp="#cdl2013">καὶ τά<unclear>φ</unclear>ο<supplied reason="lost">ς καὶ</supplied> σορός</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#pacho1827"><orig>καιτατο</orig><gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/>τ<gap reason="lost" quantity="7" unit="character"/>ος</rdg>
                    <rdg resp="#CIG">καὶ τὰ <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Ceci est le compartiment personnel d'Alkanor, ainsi que sa tombe et son cercueil.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>This is Alkanor's own recess, his burial place and his casket.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> Questa è la nicchia personale di Alkanor, la sua tomba e la sua bara.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>هذا هو الركن أو التجويف الخاص بألكانور، مكان دفنه ونعشه.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>For this tomb (not seen by Cassels), see <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn2007"/>, p. <citedRange>89</citedRange></bibl>, who described and named it ‘Red Tomb'.</p>
                <p>The word <foreign xml:lang="grc">ὀπά</foreign> means 'insight, opening'. Besides this example, it is also used in four instances, out of which three clearly mention lintels 
                    of monumental doors (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr020700</ref>, <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr022400</ref>, <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr017300</ref>, 
                    <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr096800</ref>).</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
